Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

402a41a4-6025-4bf6-bae0-82ab048180b6.7b9f3952-873f-4e99-a875-00c37abd66d6.description=Performs a statistical operation on the given table's columns. Inputs\: table - The tale to analyze. rowDelimiter - A delimiter that separates rows in the table. columnDelimiter - A delimiter that separates columns in the table. header-A columnDelimiter separated list of The names of columns. rowNames - The name of each row of data. Returns\: An html formatted statisticall analysis of the table. ExtraResults\: means - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column means. medians - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column medians. stddevs - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column standard deviations. zValues - A columnDelimiter separated list of the column z values. Responses\: success - the operation completed successfully. failure - failed to process the list or something went wrong. 402a41a4-6025-4bf6-bae0-82ab048180b6.9153d0d7-ab66-4462-b012-90e24e71be80.prompt=password 402a41a4-6025-4bf6-bae0-82ab048180b6.a367ce4f-4f21-4b39-b276-8ba5ccd55003.description=Iterates through a list of values. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration. 402a41a4-6025-4bf6-bae0-82ab048180b6.a9affa08-a12f-40a8-8c06-516139d4b303.prompt=Percentage of packet loss that is considered acceptable. 402a41a4-6025-4bf6-bae0-82ab048180b6.c707a9da-5815-41db-a489-a5a7bef29ff9.prompt=hosts to perform test from (comma delimiter) 402a41a4-6025-4bf6-bae0-82ab048180b6.d3ff5b44-d5da-460a-9136-1cb652d0fa30.prompt=Notification method 402a41a4-6025-4bf6-bae0-82ab048180b6.dce575a7-9977-43c1-88c0-c79920ebabe4.prompt=Threshold for maximum acceptable average latency 402a41a4-6025-4bf6-bae0-82ab048180b6.description=
Checks to see whether or not a connection exists, and if it exists checks to see if it is adequately reliable. Diagnoses what is wrong with the connection from multiple hosts..

Inputs\:
hosts - a comma separated list of the hosts to ping from.
target - the host to ping
delimiter - The delimiter for hosts.
lossThreshold - What percentage of packet loss you consider to be acceptable for this connection.
latencyThreshold - How long (in milliseconds) you consider to be an acceptable latency for this connection.
diagnostic so far - The result of previous diagnosis, used for chaining.
maxhops - How many hops traceroute diagnostic will descend.
notifyMethod - How to report the diagnostic.
username - username for hosts.
password - password for hosts.

Responses\:
success - no problems found.
diagnosed - problems found.
failure - something went wrong.

Recommended Thresholds\:

Connection Type		Loss Threshold (%)	Latency Threshold (ms)
DSL modem			2		200
Cable modem		2		200
dialup modem		2		500
ISDN Line			2		150
T1/T3/OCR			2		80
10 ethernet			2		10
Wireless			2		600
